 People in traditional costume perform during the 49th International Folklore Festival in Vilnius, Lithuania, on May 29, 2022. The 49th International Folklore Festival, one of the few authentic ethnic music festivals in Europe, wrapped up here in Vilnius on Sunday. (Xinhua/Xue Dongmei)  People in traditional costume perform during the 49th International Folklore Festival in Vilnius, Lithuania, on May 27, 2022. The 49th International Folklore Festival, one of the few authentic ethnic music festivals in Europe, wrapped up here in Vilnius on Sunday. (Xinhua/Xue Dongmei)  People in traditional costume perform during the 49th International Folklore Festival in Vilnius, Lithuania, on May 27, 2022. The 49th International Folklore Festival, one of the few authentic ethnic music festivals in Europe, wrapped up here in Vilnius on Sunday. (Xinhua/Xue Dongmei)  A folklore ensemble concert is held during the 49th International Folklore Festival in Vilnius, Lithuania, on May 28, 2022. The 49th International Folklore Festival, one of the few authentic ethnic music festivals in Europe, wrapped up here in Vilnius on Sunday. (Xinhua/Xue Dongmei)  Children in traditional costume perform during the 49th International Folklore Festival in Vilnius, Lithuania, on May 29, 2022. The 49th International Folklore Festival, one of the few authentic ethnic music festivals in Europe, wrapped up here in Vilnius on Sunday. (Xinhua/Xue Dongmei)  Children in traditional costume perform during the 49th International Folklore Festival in Vilnius, Lithuania, on May 29, 2022. The 49th International Folklore Festival, one of the few authentic ethnic music festivals in Europe, wrapped up here in Vilnius on Sunday. (Xinhua/Xue Dongmei)